Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Carter and Ford face conventions
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03z9b5b
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 13 Jun 1976
Presidential hopeful Jimmy Carter faces friendly Democrat convention; sitting President Ford faces tougher battle at Republican gathering. This archive edition of Letter from America was recorded by one of two listeners, who between them taped and labelled over 650 Letter From America programmes from 1973 to 1989. It was restored by the BBC in 2014. Show less